HEADWORD: Privateness
<hw>Pri"vate*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Seclusion from company or society; retirement;
privacy; secrecy.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of one not invested with public
office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Privation</ent>⟦br⟧
